    <comment>HPSF (LF) Viskores is the successor of VTK-m,  a toolkit developed by ORNL and Kitware with contributors from other national labs/universities of scientific visualization algorithms for emerging processor architectures.

While by itself is a great addition, Viskores is an important dependency of VTK and ParaView that superpower its data filters making them multithreaded with different backends including CPU and GPU.</comment>
